  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can follow these steps to regain access to your account:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook login page**:\n   - Open your browser and navigate to [www.facebook.com](https://www.facebook.com).\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgotten password?\"**:\n   - Below the password field, you will see the link \"Forgotten password?\" Click on that.\n\n3. **Identify your account**:\n   - Facebook will prompt you to enter the email address, phone number, username, or full name associated with your account. Enter the required information and click on \"Search.\"\n\n4. **Choose your recovery method**:\n   - Facebook will show you a list of options to receive a code to reset your password. This can be via email or SMS. Choose the method you prefer and click \"Continue.\"\n\n5. **Check your email or SMS**:\n   - Facebook will send a code to the email address or phone number you selected. Retrieve the code from your email or SMS.\n\n6. **Enter the code**:\n   - Go back to the Facebook page where you left off and enter the code you received. Click \"Continue.\"\n\n7. **Set a new password**:\n   - Once the code is verified, you will be prompted to enter a new password. Make sure to choose a strong and unique password that you haven't used before. Enter the new password and confirm it.\n\n8. **Log in with your new password**:\n   - After successfully resetting your password, you can log in to your Facebook account using the new password.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can visit the Facebook Help Center for additional assistance: [Facebook Help Center](https://www.facebook.com/help/).\n\nRemember to keep your email account secure, as it is vital for account recovery processes.",
